Patch 0080 — addresses user feedback: "still showing same crap. Ryzen
gaming deal as latest MEMORY_INFRA signal? Why aren't real CPU/HBM
bottleneck articles surfacing? Make it live, not stale."

THREE QUALITY ISSUES FIXED

(1) RYZEN GAMING DEALS POLLUTING THE LEDGER
    Tom's Hardware "Save $290 on Ryzen 7 9800X3D + 32GB DDR5" was
    accumulating evidence in MEMORY_INFRA because DDR5/Samsung 9100 Pro
    matched the semantic graph tokens — but it's not a bottleneck signal.

    Fix: at recordEvidence() write time, articles must pass BOTH:
      - structural_state ∈ {BOTTLENECK, CAPACITY_EXPANSION,
        SUPPLY_RESPONSE, CAPEX_BUILDOUT, DEMAND_SURGE, POLICY_SUPPORT}
        OR article_type=BOTTLENECK
        OR title/desc contains bottleneck-language (shortage, tight,
        queue, capacity constraint, binding, allocation, pricing power,
        lead time, framework, backlog, chokepoint, sole-source)
      - title/desc does NOT contain retail-deal language (save $,
        deal, combo, bundle, coupon, %off, prime day, review:, gift guide)

    Bumped KV key evidence:v1: → evidence:v2: so the polluted ledger
    starts clean.

(2) GENERIC SYSTEM-NODE NAMES ARE OPAQUE
    "MEMORY INFRA" / "FABRICATION INFRA" doesn't tell the user what
    actual bottleneck this is. Added BOTTLENECK_LABEL map:
      COMPUTE_INFRA      → "AI COMPUTE / GPU"
      MEMORY_INFRA       → "HBM / DRAM SUPPLY"
      PACKAGING_INFRA    → "CoWoS / ADV PACKAGING"
      FABRICATION_INFRA  → "TSMC / FAB CAPACITY"
      INTERCONNECT_INFRA → "OPTICAL / 800G+ FABRIC"
      COOLING_INFRA      → "LIQUID COOLING (AI)"
      ENERGY_INFRA       → "GRID / TRANSFORMERS"
      NUCLEAR_INFRA      → "NUCLEAR / HALEU / SMR"
      DEFENSE_INFRA      → "DEFENCE / MISSILES"
      RESOURCE_SCARCITY  → "RARE EARTHS / CRITICAL MIN"
      ... 20 entries total
    Each with a 1-line sub-explanation rendered under the title.

(3) "LATEST" SAMPLE WAS JUST MOST-RECENT — got Ryzen deals
    Replaced with smart pick: rank top_samples by tier (PRIMARY/
    SPECIALIST > GENERALIST > everything), tie-break by recency.
    Returns best_specialist_sample. UI now shows "Top signal:" with
    the highest-quality match — SemiAnalysis HBM article surfaces
    instead of Tom's Hardware deal.

Cache key v26 → v27. KV key evidence:v1 → evidence:v2. tsc clean.

Combined with the 0080 write-time filter, this means:
  - Ryzen deals never accumulate (filtered at write)
  - HBM / CoWoS / TSMC articles from SemiAnalysis / TrendForce /
    Digitimes / Power-Eng accumulate (specialist + bottleneck-language)
  - The panel shows real bottleneck readings with proper labels and
    the actual high-quality contributing article
